      <prefercite id="aspace_0b2f122e9d20dd38885bbe5efeb50ac8">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Palestinian Liberation Movement Collection (MS 1701). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7f1dd8d13da766215fcc4a79587a91ce">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of posters, photographs of posters, and a photographic postcard portfolio entitled "Intifada: Occupied Territory taken by eight Italian Photographers," documenting the twenty-fifth anniversary of the Palestine National Liberation Movement, the first anniversary of the Palestine State Proclamation, the second anniversary of the Intifada, and other issues and events concerning Palestinian movements. An addition to the collection includes posters relating primarily to the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine (P.F.L.P.) and similar organizations.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
  
